<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-13T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/954: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morrow</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-13T18:00:00-06:00">August 13, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>310. Department’s 440, August 13, 3 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d538fn15">Not printed.</note> Saw Estrada again yesterday. He sees no
                            objection to formula Department’s 435, August 7, 5 p.m. and Embassy’s
                            August 6, 7 p.m. He has not however been able to see President who is
                            out of the city. We will see Estrada again tomorrow and report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morrow</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>